HEADWORD: Ossified
<hw>Os"si*fied</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Changed to bone or
something resembling bone; hardened by deposits of mineral matter of any
kind; -- said of tissues.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ossifrage</ent>⟦br⟧
